# Phase labeling

When expanding VMS template or intake fields **after the June 2026 expansion**, label work explicitly:

| Phase | Goal |
|-------|------|
| **A** | Map collected data to template tags (`docxBuilder` + registry docs) |
| **B** | Add intake UI + DB + PATCH for fields not yet collected |
| **C** | Enrich via Gemini parse + resume text for snapshot/experience blocks |

Do not add template tags without a data source plan (see `docs/VMS-FIELD-MANIFEST.md`).

**Ordering (flexible):**
- **A** follows once a data source exists (DB, parse, or wizard).
- **B** and **C** may interleave: Phase C (Gemini schema) can ship before Phase B wizard UI when parse prefills and wizard collects gaps manually (gap review).
- Prefer completing docxBuilder wiring (A) in the same PR or immediately after the data source lands.

State which phase a PR covers in title or description. Historical PR sequence: `docs/archive/VMS-FULL-COVERAGE-PLAN-2026-05-EXECUTION.md`.
